This paper is about improving email search ranking models by incorporating unsupervised query type information. The main focus is on information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are covered by the cs.IR and cs.CL sub-categories. The paper also proposes neural models, which fall under the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multi-task learning, which is a topic of interest in the cs.SI sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
